  "text": "Considering LePine and Van Dyne's (2001:326) definition of voice, conceptualized as \"constructive change-oriented communication intended to improve the situation\" and [CITATION_1] 403) definition of taking charge, which refers to those \"voluntary and constructive efforts to affect organizationally functional change\", [CITATION_2] re-elaborates the change-oriented OCB definition offered by [CITATION_3] . According to Choi, change-oriented OCB refers to the \"constructive efforts by individuals to identify and implement changes with respect to work methods, policies, and procedures to improve the situation and performance\" (Choi, 2007: 469) .",
